The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | STATISTICAL HIGHLIGHTS
                                                                                                                       7                                      STATISTICAL HIGHLIGHTS
                      
	 Shikhar Dhawan and Saurabh Tiwary become 188 and 189th player to represent India in ODIs. In fact they are the 9th and 10th players to debut for India in 2010 alone.         
	 Michael Clarke registered his 5th ODI hundred and his 2nd vs India         
	 Clarke also bettered the highest score by an Australian captain on Indian soil. The previous highest was 108* by Ricky Ponting, at Bangalore (November 12, 2003).         
	 Shikhar Dhawan became the 21st Indian to record a duck in his debut innings of an ODI. He is the 7th Indian opening batsmen to do so.         
	 Virat Kohlis century was this third in ODIs and his first against Australia. Its interesting to note that all three of Kohlis hundreds have come while chasing and have resulted in wins for India.         
	 M.S. Dhoni now has 6 ducks in ODIs four of them have been first ball ducks.         
	 This is Indias biggest successful run chase against Australia in ODIs. The previous highest India successfully chased was 275/4, in Sharjah (April 24, 1998).         
	 The win was M.S. Dhonis 50th as captain in ODIs. Only Azharuddin (90) and Sourav Ganguly (76) have more wins.         
	Mohandas Menon                                                                                                                       
